text: The ResNet cap is currently 200 gigabytes per each 7 day period of combined incoming and outgoing traffic
Internet is limited to 3 Mbps per host
Guests' network is rate-limited to 5 Mb/s per user
The system passively monitors the network throughput when traffic is light
CounterStrike server is blocked by the University firewall

If a students is in obvious violations of copyright law by using a room's wired connection (i.e. ResNet) to distribute copyrighted materials, the room's connection will be disabled, and the issue could be sent to Housing Student Judicial Affairs
University Housing monitors only the amount of traffic
Students have a quota of 5 GB per day. The quota is reset at 6am
There is a 6 GB per 24-hour period upload or download data transfer limit starting at midnight of each day, on all of your combined traffic on ResNet and UIC wireless
When a total of 18 gigabytes of data is reached, the individual's bandwidth rate limit is set to 2 Mbps
Students data limit is 100 GB per week
Students have 200 GB of Free monthly usage
Currently, the University of Illinois does not have any rate limits set in place
Quotas for students are 5000 Megabyte per hr download and 2000 Megabyte per hr upload
No individual service or system running on the wired/wireless network should use more than 10 gigabytes of per day, regardless of whether it is inbound or outbound over the commodity network link
The system will trigger an overuse notification if the  average for either inbound or outbound usage exceeds 10 GB per week
Faculty members have 500 Gb per week of free network use
P2P application is separately capped at 30 Mbps for the entire campus
You may not run FTP, telnet, peer-to-peer, HTTP, IRC, DNS and mail servers on ResNet or UIC wireless-connected devices
Students 10 GB a day download quotas are on 10 AM to Midnight
The individual will have a 4 Mbps bandwidth rate limit
Guests cannot run any file sharing/downloading program
FTP and SFTP traffic is allowed for all students
FTP server is allowed by the University firewall
